description: UK Prime Minister Theresa May calls for general election on June 8
maintext:
U.K. Prime Minister Theresa May said she will hold a vote in Parliament on Wednesday to call for a general election on June 8.
May made the announcement in brief remarks outside 10 Downing Street on Tuesday.
May replaced David Cameron when he resigned the day after he lost the Brexit referendum vote in June of last year.
This is a breaking news story. Please check back for updates.
title: UK Prime Minister Theresa May calls for general election on June 8
